1.What is Bootstrap, and why is it useful for website design?
->Bootstrap is a popular front-end framework used to build responsive and mobile-first websites. It includes a collection of pre-designed components, CSS styles, JavaScript plugins, and utility classes that make it easier to create modern, professional-looking web pages.

2.Explain the Bootstrap grid system and how it helps create responsive layouts.
->The Bootstrap grid system is a flexible layout structure that uses rows and columns to help developers design responsive webpages. It is built on a 12-column layout that automatically adjusts based on screen size, allowing websites to look good on any deviceâ€”from large desktop monitors to mobile phones.

3.List and explain at least three Bootstrap components.
->Navbar :- The navbar is a responsive navigation bar used to display menus, branding, links, and search bars.Automatically collapses into a toggle menu on small screens.
->Cards :- A card is a flexible content container used to display information in a structured box. It can include text, images, buttons, lists, or links.
-> Buttons :- Bootstrap provides pre-styled buttons with different colors, sizes, and shapes.Variety of styles: primary, secondary, danger, warning, success, etc.